02:33.070 --> 02:35.990
Patricius' success at spreading the word

02:36.031 --> 02:38.242
would eventually make him a legend.

02:40.744 --> 02:44.665
Today we refer to him as Saint Patrick.

02:45.749 --> 02:47.710
But on that day,

02:47.751 --> 02:52.131
his mission was overwhelmed
by the spirit of the wolf.

02:52.172 --> 02:55.551
[WOLF HOWLING]

02:57.428 --> 03:01.223
I'm Aaron Mahnke, and this is Lore.

03:13.569 --> 03:15.863
To most of us now,

03:15.905 --> 03:17.323
werewolves are movie monsters.

03:17.364 --> 03:19.033
[SCREAMING]

03:23.704 --> 03:27.291
Whoever is bitten by
a werewolf and lives

03:27.333 --> 03:30.044
becomes a werewolf himself.

03:30.085 --> 03:32.004
Aw, don't hand me that.

03:32.046 --> 03:36.175
Hollywood has made
some 100 werewolf films

03:36.216 --> 03:38.886
since the first in 1913.

03:38.928 --> 03:40.554
I could have sworn I hit him dead on.

03:40.596 --> 03:42.181
- And I, too.
- Have you forgotten

03:42.222 --> 03:44.600
it takes a silver bullet for a werewolf?

03:44.642 --> 03:47.019
But there was a time when the werewolf

03:47.061 --> 03:49.355
was believed to be all too real.

03:51.148 --> 03:53.734
In the 15th and 16th centuries,

03:53.776 --> 03:55.486
Europe was on fire

03:55.527 --> 03:57.613
with fears of the werewolf.

03:57.655 --> 04:01.825
Tens of thousands were
accused of being wolf-men.

04:03.285 --> 04:05.245
The people of Bedburg believed

04:05.287 --> 04:08.540
they were being hunted by
one of those werewolves.

04:11.293 --> 04:13.712
It had evaded capture for years.

04:15.923 --> 04:20.219
Townspeople vanished,
never to be seen again.

04:22.972 --> 04:25.307
The people here coped
as best as they could,

04:25.349 --> 04:28.185
never knowing when the
creature would strike.

04:39.738 --> 04:41.699
[HOWLING]

04:41.740 --> 04:43.867
[PANTING]

05:04.096 --> 05:05.973
MAN: Greta.

05:06.015 --> 05:08.267
I was worried. It's getting late.

05:08.308 --> 05:09.727
[SIGH]

05:11.895 --> 05:13.522
Father, you scared me.

05:15.232 --> 05:17.735
You look so much like
your mother right now.

05:17.776 --> 05:20.237
And you work as hard as she did.

05:24.283 --> 05:28.328
A child your age. It's unfair.

05:29.538 --> 05:30.831
Did you hear

05:30.873 --> 05:32.624
about Herr Stubbe's cow being killed?

05:37.671 --> 05:40.883
Anna Christian has invited
me to Mass this evening.

05:40.924 --> 05:43.510
The moon, it will be
turning full tonight.

05:43.552 --> 05:45.304
Tonight.

05:47.222 --> 05:48.849
I cannot lose you, Greta.

05:49.933 --> 05:52.019
[SNARLING]

05:52.061 --> 05:54.605
It may sound strange
that they really thought

05:54.646 --> 05:56.815
a werewolf was stalking them.

05:58.400 --> 06:01.570
But we do know that
wolf-like humans exist.

06:03.238 --> 06:06.200
A condition known as hypertrichosis...

06:06.241 --> 06:08.702
it causes excessive hair growth.

06:08.744 --> 06:10.704
But the only thing out of control

06:10.746 --> 06:12.414
about the people afflicted

06:12.456 --> 06:14.666
is their body hair, not their behavior.

06:14.708 --> 06:17.711
There is, however, a
rare psychiatric condition

06:17.753 --> 06:19.546
called clinical lycanthropy

06:19.588 --> 06:21.215
that causes people to believe

06:21.256 --> 06:23.217
they've turned into animals.

06:23.258 --> 06:25.302
This delusion can manifest itself

06:25.344 --> 06:27.137
through animal-like behavior

06:27.179 --> 06:29.306
such as howling and clawing.

06:32.309 --> 06:34.061
In Northern Europe

06:34.103 --> 06:36.522
around the time of
the events in Bedburg,

06:36.563 --> 06:39.316
rumors began circulating of men

06:39.358 --> 06:41.693
who did more than behave like wolves,

06:41.735 --> 06:43.570
they became wolves.

06:44.988 --> 06:46.657
These wolf-men were said

06:46.698 --> 06:48.367
to attack unsuspecting victims

06:48.408 --> 06:50.494
as they walked alone in the woods.

06:52.538 --> 06:54.373
They'd mount their backs,

06:54.414 --> 06:56.583
lick their mouths and faces,

06:56.625 --> 06:58.127
and then devour them.

07:02.214 --> 07:03.799
According to legend,

07:03.841 --> 07:06.677
ONE THING ALWAYS GAVE A WEREWOLF AWAY:

07:06.718 --> 07:09.513
werewolves didn't have tails

07:09.555 --> 07:12.891
because they were just men, cursed men.

07:14.560 --> 07:16.436
One of the oldest werewolf legends

07:16.478 --> 07:18.939
can be traced back to its first telling,

07:18.981 --> 07:20.607
2,000 years ago,

07:20.649 --> 07:23.193
somewhere between Europe
and the Middle East.

07:23.235 --> 07:25.195
It's a story told to children

07:25.237 --> 07:28.031
about a creature that
devours a family...

07:28.073 --> 07:29.533
a grandmother...

07:31.034 --> 07:33.412
and a little girl in a red hood.

07:35.956 --> 07:37.666
In some versions,

07:37.708 --> 07:39.710
the wolf tricks the
girl into eating a meal

07:39.751 --> 07:42.379
made of her grandmother's corpse

07:42.421 --> 07:44.923
before seducing and devouring her.

07:44.965 --> 07:47.301
[MUNCHING]

07:47.342 --> 07:49.094
There the story ends

07:49.136 --> 07:52.306
with the monster satisfied

07:52.347 --> 07:54.808
and ready to hunt for its next victim.

07:56.435 --> 07:59.354
[HOWLING]

08:05.944 --> 08:08.739
MAN: The moon...

08:08.780 --> 08:10.699
it will be turning full tonight.

08:13.619 --> 08:15.579
I cannot lose you, Greta.

08:19.917 --> 08:22.336
[GROWLING IN DISTANCE]

08:23.503 --> 08:25.380
[RUSTLING]

08:25.422 --> 08:26.673
[SNARLING]

08:26.715 --> 08:27.758
Papa?

08:32.554 --> 08:34.014
Who is there?

08:36.308 --> 08:38.727
- [GROWLING]
- [GASP]

08:51.573 --> 08:54.076
[SNARLING]

08:54.117 --> 08:58.413
[SCREAMING]

09:47.045 --> 09:49.548
Ten years after Greta was attacked,

09:49.589 --> 09:52.050
the people of Bedburg still lived

09:52.092 --> 09:54.219
in fear of the mysterious beast.

09:57.180 --> 09:59.725
Peter Stubbe, a town leader,

09:59.766 --> 10:02.394
could only offer grim words of caution.

10:03.687 --> 10:06.356
You know the evil that preys on us.

10:06.398 --> 10:09.318
The wolf that mutilates our cattle

10:09.359 --> 10:12.029
and attacked Greta Helfelderz

10:12.070 --> 10:14.865
is no creation of God.

10:14.906 --> 10:17.117
The animal we hunt

10:17.159 --> 10:21.913
is a creation and servant of the devil.

10:21.955 --> 10:23.457
[CROWD MURMURING]

10:23.498 --> 10:25.208
If you value your life,

10:25.250 --> 10:28.128
you will stay inside with
your doors barricaded.

10:29.463 --> 10:31.048
For Greta's friend Celeste,

10:31.089 --> 10:34.384
Stubbe's advice was an unwelcome warning

10:34.426 --> 10:36.595
because that night, for her,

10:36.636 --> 10:39.890
there was one emotion
more potent than fear.

10:41.391 --> 10:42.392
- Wah-wah!
- Aah!

10:42.434 --> 10:43.518
[LAUGHING]

10:44.770 --> 10:46.271
[CHUCKLE]

10:46.313 --> 10:47.898
Nils.

10:47.939 --> 10:49.399
[KISS]

10:50.567 --> 10:52.152
I was afraid you wouldn't come.

10:52.194 --> 10:54.446
I snuck out of the house.

10:56.573 --> 10:58.825
We're leaving in the
morning for Bergheim.

11:01.036 --> 11:03.580
There's no work for
my father in Bedburg.

11:03.622 --> 11:05.874
All the townspeople are
afraid to do business here.

11:05.916 --> 11:08.668
People are afraid to stay.

11:08.710 --> 11:10.921
I want you to leave with us.

11:12.464 --> 11:14.299
My mother needs me.

11:18.678 --> 11:21.139
You must stay for your mother.

11:21.181 --> 11:23.767
I must go for my father.

11:27.062 --> 11:28.146
MAN: Help me.

11:30.148 --> 11:32.442
Please help.

11:32.484 --> 11:34.069
That's not a wolf.

11:35.362 --> 11:36.613
It's human.

11:36.655 --> 11:38.657
Somebody, anybody, hurry.

11:38.698 --> 11:39.991
They need help.

11:41.243 --> 11:42.619
No.

11:42.661 --> 11:44.329
Wait here.

11:52.629 --> 11:53.922
MAN: Help me.

12:03.557 --> 12:06.643
Help me. Please, help.

12:08.395 --> 12:09.896
Nils?

12:20.365 --> 12:22.617
Nils?

12:22.659 --> 12:24.703
Help. Please come quickly.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.496
Nils?

12:26.538 --> 12:28.707
Help me! Please!

12:32.836 --> 12:33.837
Nils?

12:35.130 --> 12:36.756
Did you find him?

12:36.798 --> 12:39.301
MAN: Help, please!

12:49.394 --> 12:51.897
[TRICKLING]

13:08.371 --> 13:11.041
[GASP, SHUDDERING]

13:15.128 --> 13:17.380
[SNARLING]

13:23.929 --> 13:25.430
[SNARLING]

13:27.766 --> 13:29.726
Aah!

13:40.862 --> 13:42.155
I heard a scream.

13:42.197 --> 13:44.824
Stay in the house. Barricade the door.

13:47.410 --> 13:48.411
Do it.

13:53.792 --> 13:57.837
[HOWLING]

14:06.054 --> 14:07.597
It's Nils.

14:08.682 --> 14:09.849
Look.

14:14.688 --> 14:15.897
[MUTTERS]

14:15.939 --> 14:17.691
[PANTING]

14:21.695 --> 14:23.280
It spoke.

14:24.948 --> 14:27.033
She said...

14:27.075 --> 14:30.036
the wolf... spoke.

14:33.790 --> 14:36.459
AARON MAHNKE: In the remote
French province of Gevaudan,

14:36.501 --> 14:40.297
people were absolutely sure
of what was hunting them.

14:40.338 --> 14:44.634
Between 1764 and 1767,

14:44.676 --> 14:46.886
there were killings that
could only be explained

14:46.928 --> 14:50.223
by a creature not of this world,

14:50.265 --> 14:54.519
a beast that was hunting
women and children,

14:54.561 --> 14:57.606
crushing their heads
and decapitating them

14:57.647 --> 14:59.858
and drinking their blood.

14:59.899 --> 15:03.111
Many claimed to have seen the creature.

15:03.153 --> 15:06.114
Their descriptions varied wildly...

15:06.156 --> 15:08.825
a wolf as large as a horse,

15:08.867 --> 15:11.328
a dog-dragon hybrid,

15:11.369 --> 15:15.165
A LOUP GAROU: a wolf-man.

15:15.206 --> 15:17.459
The Bishop of Mende expressed

15:17.500 --> 15:19.169
what most of the people here

15:19.210 --> 15:21.004
already knew in their hearts...

15:21.046 --> 15:23.089
the ferocious beast was a monster

15:23.131 --> 15:24.841
sent to punish the sinful.

15:27.802 --> 15:29.346
The Bishop decreed

15:29.387 --> 15:31.890
that only penance would
placate God's wrath.

15:31.931 --> 15:34.809
But after a month of religious rites,

15:34.851 --> 15:38.063
the beast continued to kill...

15:38.104 --> 15:42.317
as many as 100 in just three years.

15:42.359 --> 15:46.196
Finally, the King ordered
his royal gun bearer

15:46.237 --> 15:49.866
François Antoine to put
an end to the carnage.

15:49.908 --> 15:51.493
[DOGS BARKING]

15:51.534 --> 15:53.745
After a pursuit that
lasted for months...

15:53.787 --> 15:55.288
[BARKING CONTINUES]

15:55.330 --> 15:57.248
Antoine claimed to have shot the beast.

15:57.290 --> 15:58.583
[GUNSHOT]

15:58.625 --> 16:00.794
[ANIMAL MOANING]

16:03.755 --> 16:07.133
He sent the carcass to be
displayed at Versailles.

16:07.175 --> 16:11.012
There it was met with
great disenchantment.

16:11.054 --> 16:15.934
This wasn't a beast crafted
from God's own anger.

16:15.975 --> 16:18.478
People had envisioned a monster.

16:19.604 --> 16:20.939
But what they got

16:20.980 --> 16:23.525
was just... nature.

16:27.320 --> 16:31.116
Christ, our Lord, save us.

16:31.157 --> 16:33.743
Expurg our people.

16:35.453 --> 16:38.748
Two more of our children are dead.

16:38.790 --> 16:41.000
There will not be another.

16:41.042 --> 16:44.921
Salvation belongs to the Lord. Amen.

17:04.315 --> 17:06.651
We'll bring you back the beast's head.

17:06.693 --> 17:08.694
Bring back your own.

17:08.737 --> 17:11.364
You need to be here for your Greta.

17:11.406 --> 17:14.867
Knowing the beast is dead
will be enough for me.

17:19.830 --> 17:24.085
Jens, pardon my intrusion,

17:24.127 --> 17:28.631
but you must be concerned
about leaving Greta all alone.

17:30.675 --> 17:32.385
Very much, Herr Stubbe.

17:32.427 --> 17:34.763
If you feel comfortable,

17:34.804 --> 17:37.348
let her stay with me until
you've killed the wolf.

17:40.685 --> 17:42.937
My home is hers.

17:54.699 --> 17:56.451
I'm afraid.

17:56.493 --> 17:58.203
I am, too.

18:00.497 --> 18:02.791
I feel better knowing you're not alone.

18:21.601 --> 18:26.189
I don't care how fierce this wolf is.

18:26.231 --> 18:29.609
It has never faced 20 men from Bedburg.

18:31.152 --> 18:32.570
Let's go inside.

19:06.938 --> 19:09.399
[GROWLING]

19:16.489 --> 19:18.241
[SNARLING]

19:18.283 --> 19:19.868
[SCREAMING]

19:19.909 --> 19:22.161
You look unwell, Greta.

19:24.664 --> 19:26.875
- I haven't been sleeping.
- Hmm.

19:26.916 --> 19:29.043
Every time I close my eyes I...

19:29.085 --> 19:32.839
You see the night ten years ago?

19:35.091 --> 19:38.511
The dreams have increased lately.

19:38.553 --> 19:40.346
I don't know why.

19:42.515 --> 19:45.977
They even... come to me when I'm awake.

19:51.608 --> 19:53.026
[GROWLING]

19:59.866 --> 20:02.076
[GROWLING]

20:12.462 --> 20:13.963
[PANTING]

20:37.570 --> 20:39.155
[SNARLING]

20:50.249 --> 20:51.709
Oh, Greta.

20:53.252 --> 20:56.965
I've waited ten years for this moment.

20:58.383 --> 21:00.760
To have you all to myself...

21:02.053 --> 21:03.471
again.

21:04.597 --> 21:05.682
Again?

21:09.352 --> 21:11.104
JENS: Check its paw.

21:25.159 --> 21:27.078
This is not the creature.

21:28.538 --> 21:30.331
It would have a scar...

21:31.874 --> 21:35.086
a mark where Greta stabbed it.

21:50.768 --> 21:52.270
[PANTING]

21:52.311 --> 21:54.772
[SCREAMING]

22:05.575 --> 22:09.787
You have no idea of the
trouble you caused me.

22:13.624 --> 22:15.668
I had to leave Bedburg for months

22:15.710 --> 22:17.712
while my hand healed.

22:17.754 --> 22:22.383
I knew that wearing gloves
at all times might be noticed.

22:22.425 --> 22:25.803
But, if an accident also
rendered me a cripple,

22:25.845 --> 22:27.430
no one could imagine

22:27.472 --> 22:33.728
that bent, broke Peter
Stubbe could also be the wolf.

22:40.860 --> 22:43.821
Oh, Greta,

22:43.863 --> 22:45.990
you were the one that got away.

22:51.829 --> 22:53.706
[WHIMPERING]

23:00.004 --> 23:01.714
But wolves are patient.

23:02.840 --> 23:04.634
They are opportunists,

23:04.675 --> 23:06.719
tracking their prey,

23:06.761 --> 23:09.013
waiting until the moment is just right.

23:12.308 --> 23:14.977
And that's...

23:15.019 --> 23:16.854
when they attack.

23:20.733 --> 23:22.401
My father knows I'm here.

23:22.443 --> 23:25.947
Your father knows you were here.

23:33.496 --> 23:36.124
[PANTING]

23:43.214 --> 23:44.382
- No.
- Aah!

23:44.423 --> 23:46.050
No.

23:46.092 --> 23:47.969
[GIBBERING]

23:48.010 --> 23:49.387
Aah!

23:52.306 --> 23:55.393
Listen, I think I'll keep this one.

23:56.727 --> 23:58.688
It seems only fair.

24:04.735 --> 24:06.529
Aah... Oh!

24:11.284 --> 24:12.577
Father!

24:12.618 --> 24:15.163
Aah! No!

24:28.467 --> 24:29.886
Greta!

24:34.473 --> 24:36.517
It was you.

24:36.559 --> 24:37.685
[PANTING]

24:37.727 --> 24:38.853
You're the wolf.

24:48.112 --> 24:49.739
You have to be careful.

24:49.780 --> 24:51.574
You have to watch where
you go now, you know,

24:51.616 --> 24:54.368
how late you stay
out, and it scares you.

24:54.410 --> 24:56.537
An animal like this has to be caught.

24:58.748 --> 25:01.834
AARON MAHNKE: In the summer of 1977,

25:01.876 --> 25:05.087
New York City was gripped by fear.

25:05.129 --> 25:09.717
A killer was stalking
and murdering New Yorkers.

25:09.759 --> 25:12.094
This is a police sketch of the suspect

25:12.136 --> 25:14.013
in one of the nastiest murder cases

25:14.055 --> 25:15.890
New York Police have had come their way

25:15.932 --> 25:17.391
in a long time.

25:17.433 --> 25:18.768
TOM BROKAW: The past year, the killer,

25:18.809 --> 25:20.311
believed to be a young man,

25:20.353 --> 25:23.064
has killed five people and wounded four,

25:23.105 --> 25:25.858
his victims mostly young women

25:25.900 --> 25:27.610
with shoulder-length dark hair,

25:27.652 --> 25:30.154
usually shot at very close range

25:30.196 --> 25:32.573
while sitting in parked cars at night.

25:32.615 --> 25:34.450
He calls himself the Son of Sam,

25:34.492 --> 25:36.535
and he is known as
the .44 Caliber Killer

25:36.577 --> 25:38.913
because he has always
used that kind of handgun.

25:38.955 --> 25:40.873
NEWS REPORTER: Many
young brown-haired women

25:40.915 --> 25:42.375
are worried about their safety

25:42.416 --> 25:43.751
because of the .44 Caliber Killer.

25:43.793 --> 25:45.336
It's one of those crimes

25:45.378 --> 25:47.922
that's been visited upon
man throughout the ages...

25:47.964 --> 25:50.132
a demented killer.

25:50.174 --> 25:51.676
They don't know how to stop him.

25:51.717 --> 25:54.095
He sent mocking letters to the police

25:54.136 --> 25:56.347
threatening even more murders.

25:56.389 --> 25:59.767
Despite the largest
manhunt in New York history,

25:59.809 --> 26:03.062
the Son of Sam evaded
capture for months.

26:03.104 --> 26:05.106
New Yorkers felt as though

26:05.147 --> 26:08.025
they were being stalked by a monster.

26:12.697 --> 26:14.865
NEWS REPORTER: Aided by
light from a full moon,

26:14.907 --> 26:16.534
three or four eyewitnesses said

26:16.575 --> 26:18.035
they got a look at the killer.

26:18.077 --> 26:19.787
I'm very pleased to announce

26:19.829 --> 26:23.624
that the people of the City of New York

26:23.666 --> 26:26.877
can rest easy this morning

26:26.919 --> 26:32.008
because of the fact that the
police have captured a man

26:32.049 --> 26:34.343
whom they believe to be the Son of Sam.

26:34.385 --> 26:36.262
[SHOUTING]

26:36.304 --> 26:39.140
When the man was questioned,

26:39.181 --> 26:41.934
he claimed to be following
the orders of a demon

26:41.976 --> 26:43.728
in the form of a dog

26:43.769 --> 26:45.980
that belonged to his neighbor Sam.

26:47.982 --> 26:49.483
[SHOUTING]

26:49.525 --> 26:52.445
His real name was David Berkowitz.

26:52.486 --> 26:53.946
[SHOUTING]

26:53.988 --> 26:55.948
When the public finally
got a look at him,

26:55.990 --> 26:57.658
there was astonishment.

26:59.076 --> 27:01.037
This was the monster?

27:01.078 --> 27:04.206
A postal worker from the Bronx?

27:04.248 --> 27:06.459
He was just a man.

27:06.500 --> 27:09.170
He could have been
one of their neighbors.

27:09.211 --> 27:13.424
An average guy, just like them.

27:16.927 --> 27:18.346
If Son of Sam is convicted,

27:18.387 --> 27:19.597
what do you think should happen to him?

27:19.638 --> 27:20.890
I think he should be killed.

27:20.931 --> 27:22.266
I'd like to see him killed.

27:22.308 --> 27:24.769
Dead. Period.

27:28.105 --> 27:29.440
Confess your sins.

27:30.524 --> 27:31.650
[GAGGING]

27:33.110 --> 27:35.780
[COUGHING]

27:35.821 --> 27:38.783
[GASPING, WHEEZING]

27:38.824 --> 27:40.743
[COUGHING]

27:50.336 --> 27:52.713
When I was 12 years old...

27:54.298 --> 27:56.467
the devil came to me.

27:58.511 --> 28:01.013
He loved me.

28:01.055 --> 28:03.724
In exchange for my soul,

28:03.766 --> 28:07.645
he offered me anything
I desired in this life.

28:07.686 --> 28:09.814
I was transformed

28:09.855 --> 28:13.692
into a greedy, strong, and fierce wolf.

28:13.734 --> 28:16.487
For years, I fed on the blood

28:16.529 --> 28:21.325
of cattle, sheep, goats,

28:21.367 --> 28:23.160
and the flesh of men...

28:23.202 --> 28:25.955
[ONLOOKERS GASP, MURMUR]

28:25.996 --> 28:27.415
...of my own son.

28:29.792 --> 28:33.421
I would approach women

28:33.462 --> 28:37.216
as a kind man, as a father,

28:37.258 --> 28:40.136
and kill them

28:40.177 --> 28:43.055
and eat their flesh...

28:43.097 --> 28:45.182
as a wolf.

28:45.224 --> 28:47.768
CROWD: Ohh!

28:47.810 --> 28:50.229
[STUBBE CHUCKLES]

28:56.444 --> 28:59.029
[LAUGHING]

29:00.823 --> 29:03.576
[LAUGHTER GROWS LOUDER]

29:06.328 --> 29:09.957
With the citizens of
Bedburg as witnesses,

29:09.999 --> 29:12.460
Peter Stubbe was sentenced to death.

29:12.501 --> 29:15.087
He was tied to a large wheel.

29:15.129 --> 29:18.424
Large patches of his
skin were peeled off

29:18.466 --> 29:20.050
with red-hot pincers.

29:20.092 --> 29:23.053
After that, his arms
and legs were broken

29:23.095 --> 29:25.347
with the blunt end of an ax.

29:27.183 --> 29:28.809
Only then,

29:28.851 --> 29:32.313
with his skin removed
and his bones broken,

29:32.354 --> 29:34.398
did they turn the ax around

29:34.440 --> 29:36.233
and cut off his head.

29:39.445 --> 29:41.113
But we can't just dismiss

29:41.155 --> 29:43.032
the desire to witness Stubbe's execution

29:43.073 --> 29:45.534
as a relic of history.

29:47.578 --> 29:51.290
Paris, 1937.

29:51.332 --> 29:55.419
Eugene Weidmann, a German
citizen living in France,

29:55.461 --> 29:57.463
was arrested for murder,

29:57.505 --> 29:59.757
beginning with the botched kidnapping

29:59.798 --> 30:01.467
of an American tourist.

30:02.885 --> 30:04.386
Weidmann was accused

30:04.428 --> 30:06.764
of a murder spree that took six lives.

30:08.849 --> 30:12.311
The German murderer
became front-page news.

30:14.355 --> 30:17.816
His trial was a sensation.

30:17.858 --> 30:19.902
Weidmann was found guilty

30:19.944 --> 30:22.571
and sentenced to die by guillotine.

30:25.115 --> 30:28.661
And the execution would
take place in public.

30:30.538 --> 30:33.916
Going back to a tradition
from the Roman Empire,

30:33.958 --> 30:36.293
The French believed public executions

30:36.335 --> 30:39.004
served as a deterrent
to future criminals.

30:39.046 --> 30:42.758
They were a moral lesson
for the larger community.

30:42.800 --> 30:46.387
On the morning of June 17, 1939,

30:46.428 --> 30:48.764
hundreds of people gathered

30:48.806 --> 30:50.766
in front of the St. Pierre Prison.

30:52.810 --> 30:56.146
The crowd, as a Life
Magazine reporter wrote,

30:56.188 --> 30:59.775
was eager to experience
the exquisite excitement

30:59.817 --> 31:02.653
of seeing a man have his head cut off.

31:21.380 --> 31:23.924
The crowd surged toward the body.

31:26.218 --> 31:27.845
There were reports that women

31:27.886 --> 31:29.722
dipped their handkerchiefs in his blood

31:29.763 --> 31:31.223
as mementos.

31:33.100 --> 31:34.768
The execution had transformed

31:34.810 --> 31:37.021
into a macabre entertainment.

31:37.062 --> 31:40.733
Word of the crowd's behavior
circulated around the world,

31:40.774 --> 31:43.319
much to the horror of
the French authorities.

31:43.360 --> 31:45.154
One would write,

31:45.195 --> 31:47.406
"Far from serving as a deterrent,

31:47.448 --> 31:49.283
"the public execution promoted

31:49.325 --> 31:51.410
baser instincts of human nature."

31:53.329 --> 31:55.080
Weidmann would be the last man

31:55.122 --> 31:59.126
the French would publicly
execute by guillotine.

31:59.168 --> 32:05.591
Executions by guillotine
would continue until 1977,

32:05.633 --> 32:08.844
but only behind prison walls,

32:08.886 --> 32:10.638
hidden from view.

32:12.264 --> 32:13.807
In spite of this change,

32:13.849 --> 32:15.392
French authorities can't stop people

32:15.434 --> 32:17.436
from wanting to witness the spectacle

32:17.478 --> 32:18.854
of Weidmann's death.

32:21.023 --> 32:22.650
In the last ten years alone,

32:22.691 --> 32:24.360
his execution has been viewed

32:24.401 --> 32:26.737
over a million times on the internet.

32:29.948 --> 32:32.826
The people of Bedburg
mounted Peter Stubbe's head

32:32.868 --> 32:34.745
on a pole for all to see.

32:34.787 --> 32:38.248
Below the head they carved
the figure of a wolf.

32:38.290 --> 32:40.834
It's not so difficult to understand

32:40.876 --> 32:42.628
why they would want him destroyed.

32:42.670 --> 32:45.506
They believed a werewolf
had been preying on them.

32:46.757 --> 32:48.092
In a final act,

32:48.133 --> 32:50.010
they burned his body to ash

32:50.052 --> 32:52.554
so he couldn't rise again.

32:52.596 --> 32:55.307
It wasn't just revenge they were after.

32:55.349 --> 32:57.559
They believed they could vanquish evil.

32:59.228 --> 33:01.146
But wasn't that just an illusion?

33:04.400 --> 33:05.943
No matter what we do,

33:05.984 --> 33:10.072
the evil in men always seems to return.

33:10.114 --> 33:13.575
Perhaps that evil would
be easier to accept

33:13.617 --> 33:16.328
if we could blame it on werewolves

33:16.370 --> 33:20.249
because the beast, you
see, is no superstition.

33:20.290 --> 33:22.251
It's always existed

33:22.292 --> 33:25.587
and always will, inside of us.

